I am writing a wordpress theme which implements a CSS-only solution to achieve the following:

- Display a hamburger icon in the header only if user is on mobile device 

- When the hamburger icon is clicked, a sidebar on the right slides into view smoothly, whilst the landing page remains intact. The sidebar will contain custom text.

- The sidebar has a cross icon on the top right. When it is clicked, the sidebar slides out of view smoothly, restoring full view of the landing page.

I have attached header.php and style.css below.

Assess whether the desired functionality is achieved and identify mistakes in the code. 

---

FILE: header.php

<?php
// header.php

?>
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html <?php language_attributes(); ?>>
<head>
    <meta charset="<?php bloginfo( 'charset' ); ?>">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <?php wp_head(); ?>
</head>
<body <?php body_class(); ?>>

    <header>
        
        <input type="checkbox" class="toggle-sidebar" id="toggle-sidebar">

        <div class="logo">
            <?php
            if ( has_custom_logo() ) {
                the_custom_logo();
            } else {
                echo '<a href="' . esc_url( home_url( '/' ) ) . '">' . get_bloginfo( 'name' ) . '</a>';
            }
            ?>
        </div>

        <!-- Desktop Navigation -->
        <nav>
            <?php
            wp_nav_menu( array(
                'theme_location' => 'primary',
                'menu_id'        => 'primary-menu',
                'container'      => false,
                'depth'          => 2,
                'fallback_cb'    => 'wp_page_menu',
                'menu_class'     => 'primary-menu'
            ) );
            ?>
        </nav>

        <!-- Hamburger Icon for Mobile -->
        <label for="toggle-sidebar" class="hamburger">
            <span></span>
            <span></span>
            <span></span>
        </label>

        <!-- Overlay to Close Sidebar when Clicked -->
        <label for="toggle-sidebar" class="overlay"></label>

    </header>

    <!-- Sidebar for Mobile Menu -->
    <div class="sidebar">
        <label for="toggle-sidebar" class="close-btn">&times;</label>
        
        <nav>
            <?php
            // Display a different menu specifically for the sidebar
            wp_nav_menu( array(
                'theme_location' => 'mobile_sidebar', // Register this in functions.php
                'menu_id'        => 'sidebar-menu',
                'container'      => false,
                'depth'          => 2,
                'fallback_cb'    => 'wp_page_menu',
                'menu_class'     => 'sidebar-menu'
            ) );
            ?>
        </nav>
        <!-- Add any additional sidebar content here -->
        <div class="sidebar-extra-content">
            <br><br><br><br><br><br><br>
            <em>(C) Copyright 2024</em>
        </div>
    </div>

 
    <div class="main-content">
        <!-- Page content goes here -->
    </div>



---

FILE: style.css

/*
