Text Domain: my-custom-theme
*/

@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Open+Sans:400,700&display=swap');

/* CSS Variables for Color Schemes */
:root {
    /* Header and Footer */
    --header-bg: #000000;
    --header-text-light-gray: #bdbdbd;
    --header-text-very-light-gray: #d8d8d8;
    --header-text-orange: #f7931e;
    --header-text-yellow: #fec34e;
    --header-text-white: #ffffff;

    /* Landing Page Content - Darker Gray */
    --darker-gray-bg: #eaeaea;
    --darker-gray-text-orange: #ff9900;
    --darker-gray-text-gray: #676767;

    /* Landing Page Content - Lighter Gray */
    --lighter-gray-bg: #fafafa;
    --lighter-gray-text-orange1: #ff9900;
    --lighter-gray-text-dark-gray: #676767;
    --lighter-gray-text-orange2: #f7941e;
    --lighter-gray-text-blue: #4a8cf6;
    --lighter-gray-text-green: #00a857;

    /* General */
    --font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif;
}

/* Reset and Base Styles */
*,
*::before,
*::after {
    box-sizing: border-box;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
}

body {
    font-family: var(--font-family);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--lighter-gray-bg);
}

/* Fixed Header */
header {
    position: fixed;
    top: 0;
    width: 100%;
    background-color: var(--header-bg);
    color: var(--header-text-light-gray);
    padding: 10px 20px;
    z-index: 1000;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
}

header a {
    color: var(--header-text-white);
    font-weight: bold;
    text-decoration: none;
    margin-left: 15px;
}

header a:hover {
    color: var(--header-text-orange);
    font-weight: bold;
}

/* Main Content Padding to Avoid Overlap with Fixed Header */
.main-content {
    padding-top: 60px;
}

/* Section Styles */
.section {
    width: 100%;
    padding: 60px 20px;
}

.darker-gray {
    background-color: var(--darker-gray-bg);
    color: var(--darker-gray-text-gray);
}

.darker-gray h2,
.darker-gray h3 {
    color: var(--darker-gray-text-orange);
}

.lighter-gray {
    background-color: var(--lighter-gray-bg);
    color: var(--lighter-gray-text-dark-gray);
}

.lighter-gray h2,
.lighter-gray h3 {
    color: var(--lighter-gray-text-orange1);
}

.lighter-gray .highlight-orange {
    color: var(--lighter-gray-text-orange2);
}

.lighter-gray .highlight-blue {
    color: var(--lighter-gray-text-blue);
}

.lighter-gray .highlight-green {
    color: var(--lighter-gray-text-green);
}

/* Fixed Footer */
footer {
    background-color: var(--header-bg);
    color: var(--header-text-light-gray);
    text-align: center;
    padding: 20px;
    position: relative;
    width: 100%;
    clear: both;
}



/* Hamburger Menu Styles */
.hamburger {
    display: none;
    flex-direction: column;
    cursor: pointer;
    margin-left: auto;
    z-index: 2700; /* Increase z-index to ensure it's above other elements */
}

.hamburger span {
    background: var(--header-text-light-gray);
    height: 2.2px;
    width: 25px;
    margin: 2.4px 0;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
}

/* Overlay to darken the landing page */
.overlay {
    z-index: 1600;
    position: fixed;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7); /* Semi-transparent black */
    z-index: 1400;
    display: none; /* Hidden by default */
    transition: opacity 0.3s ease;
    opacity: 0;
    pointer-events: none;
}

/* Sidebar Styling */
.sidebar {
    position: fixed;
    top: 0;
    right: -300px; /* Initially hidden off-screen */
    height: 100%;
    width: 300px;
    background-color: rgba(230, 140, 20, 0.9); /* Semi-transparent sidebar */
    color: var(--header-text-white);
    box-shadow: -2px 0 5px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
    transition: right 0.3s ease;
    z-index: 1700;
    padding: 20px;
    overflow-y: auto;
}

/* Sidebar Menu Styles */
.sidebar nav {
    font-family: var(--font-family);
    margin-top: 60px; /* Adjust this value as needed for sufficient gap */
}

.sidebar-menu {
    list-style: none; /* Remove bullets */
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
}

.sidebar-menu li {
    margin-bottom: 8px; /* Space between items */
}

.sidebar-menu li a {
    color: var(--header-text-very-light-gray);  
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: bold;
    display: block;
    padding: 4px 0; /* Add padding for clickable area */
}

.sidebar-menu li a:hover {
    color: var(--header-text-white); /* Same hover effect as desktop navigation */
    font-weight: bold;
}

.sidebar-menu ul {
    list-style: none; /* Remove bullets for sub-items */
    margin-left: 40px; /* Add indentation for sub-items */
    padding: 0;
}

.sidebar-menu ul li {
    margin-bottom: 4px; /* Space between sub-items */
}

.sidebar-menu ul li a {
    color: var(--header-text-light-gray);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: bold;
    padding: 2px 0; /* Add padding for clickable area */
}

.sidebar-menu ul li a:hover {
    color: var(--header-text-white); /* Same hover effect as desktop navigation */
    font-weight: bold;
}


/* Close Button Styling */
.sidebar .close-btn {
    position: absolute;
    text-decoration: none;
    top: 5px;
    right: 20px;
    background: none;
    border: none;
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: bold;
    color: var(--header-text-light-gray);
    cursor: pointer;
    z-index: 2000; /* Ensure it appears above other elements */
    transition: color 0.3s ease;
}

.sidebar .close-btn:hover {
    color: var(--header-text-white); /* Change color on hover for better visibility */
    font-weight: bold;
    text-decoration: none;
}


/* Checkbox to toggle sidebar */
.toggle-sidebar {
    display: none;
  }
  
/* Show sidebar when checkbox is checked */
.toggle-sidebar:checked ~ .sidebar {
    right: 0;
}
  
/* Overlay Effect */
.toggle-sidebar:checked ~ .overlay {
    display: block;
    opacity: 1; /* Now the transition to this opacity will occur */
    pointer-events: auto;
}

/* Hide on mobile */
.desktop-only {
    display: block;
}

.mobile-only {
    display: none;
}

/* Desktop Navigation Styling */
header nav {
    display: flex;
}

header nav ul {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
}

header nav ul li {
    position: relative;
}

header nav ul li a {
    color: var(--header-text-white);
    padding: 10px 15px;
    display: block;
    text-decoration: none;
}

header nav ul li a:hover {
    color: var(--header-text-orange);
}

/* Submenu Styles */
header nav ul li ul {
    display: none;
    position: absolute;
    top: 100%;
    left: 0;
    background-color: var(--header-bg);
    min-width: 200px;
    z-index: 999;
}

header nav ul li:hover > ul {
    display: block;
}

header nav ul li ul li {
    width: 100%;
}

header nav ul li ul li a {
    padding: 10px 15px;
    color: var(--header-text-white);
}

header nav ul li ul li a:hover {
    background-color: var(--header-bg);
    color: var(--header-text-orange);
}


/* Responsive Design */
@media (max-width: 768px) {
    /* Mobile-specific overrides */
    
    .desktop-only {
        display: none;
    }
    
    .mobile-only {
        display: block;
    }

    header {
        flex-direction: row;
        align-items: center;
    }

    header nav {
        display: none; /* Hide the default desktop navigation */
    }

    .hamburger {
        display: flex;
    }

    .section {
        padding: 40px 10px;
    }
}

Your WordPress theme implementation aims to create a responsive, CSS-only hamburger menu that toggles a sidebar on mobile devices. While your approach is generally on the right track, there are several issues in both the `header.php` and `style.css` files that prevent the desired functionality from being fully achieved. Below is a detailed assessment of your code, highlighting the mistakes and providing recommendations for corrections.

---

## **1. HTML Structure in `header.php`**

### **Issue 1: Incorrect Placement of the Checkbox**

**Problem:**
The `<input type="checkbox" class="toggle-sidebar" id="toggle-sidebar">` is placed **inside** the `<header>` element. In your CSS, you're using the general sibling combinator (`~`) to target `.sidebar` and `.overlay` based on the state of this checkbox:

```css
.toggle-sidebar:checked ~ .sidebar { ... }
.toggle-sidebar:checked ~ .overlay { ... }
```

However, since the checkbox is nested within `<header>`, it is **not** a sibling of `.sidebar` or `.overlay`. The general sibling combinator only selects elements that share the **same parent**. In your current structure:

```html
<body>
    <header>
        <input type="checkbox" class="toggle-sidebar" id="toggle-sidebar">
        <!-- Other header content -->
    </header>
    <div class="sidebar">
        <!-- Sidebar content -->
    </div>
    <div class="main-content">
        <!-- Main content -->
    </div>
</body>
```

Here, `.toggle-sidebar` is a child of `<header>`, while `.sidebar` and `.overlay` are siblings of `<header>`. Therefore, the CSS selectors won't apply as intended.

**Solution:**
Move the checkbox **outside** the `<header>` so that it becomes a sibling of both `<header>` and `.sidebar`. This ensures that the CSS sibling combinators can correctly target `.sidebar` and `.overlay` based on the checkbox state.

**Corrected `header.php`:**

```php
<?php
// header.php
?>
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html <?php language_attributes(); ?>>
<head>
    <meta charset="<?php bloginfo( 'charset' ); ?>">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <?php wp_head(); ?>
</head>
<body <?php body_class(); ?>>

    <!-- Checkbox for toggling sidebar -->
    <input type="checkbox" class="toggle-sidebar" id="toggle-sidebar">

    <header>
        <div class="logo">
            <?php
            if ( has_custom_logo() ) {
                the_custom_logo();
            } else {
                echo '<a href="' . esc_url( home_url( '/' ) ) . '">' . get_bloginfo( 'name' ) . '</a>';
            }
            ?>
        </div>

        <!-- Desktop Navigation -->
        <nav class="desktop-only">
            <?php
            wp_nav_menu( array(
                'theme_location' => 'primary',
                'menu_id'        => 'primary-menu',
                'container'      => false,
                'depth'          => 2,
                'fallback_cb'    => 'wp_page_menu',
                'menu_class'     => 'primary-menu'
            ) );
            ?>
        </nav>

        <!-- Hamburger Icon for Mobile -->
        <label for="toggle-sidebar" class="hamburger">
            <span></span>
            <span></span>
            <span></span>
        </label>
    </header>

    <!-- Overlay to Close Sidebar when Clicked -->
    <label for="toggle-sidebar" class="overlay"></label>

    <!-- Sidebar for Mobile Menu -->
    <div class="sidebar">
        <label for="toggle-sidebar" class="close-btn">&times;</label>

        <nav>
            <?php
            // Display a different menu specifically for the sidebar
            wp_nav_menu( array(
                'theme_location' => 'mobile_sidebar', // Ensure this is registered in functions.php
                'menu_id'        => 'sidebar-menu',
                'container'      => false,
                'depth'          => 2,
                'fallback_cb'    => 'wp_page_menu',
                'menu_class'     => 'sidebar-menu'
            ) );
            ?>
        </nav>
        <!-- Add any additional sidebar content here -->
        <div class="sidebar-extra-content">
            <br><br><br><br><br><br><br>
            <em>(C) Copyright 2024</em>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="main-content">
        <!-- Page content goes here -->
    </div>

    <?php wp_footer(); ?>
</body>
</html>
```

**Key Changes:**

- Moved the `<input type="checkbox" class="toggle-sidebar" id="toggle-sidebar">` **outside** the `<header>` so that it's a direct child of `<body>`, making it a sibling to `.sidebar` and `.overlay`.
- Moved the `.overlay` label **outside** the `<header>` for the same reason.

### **Issue 2: Missing Registration of `mobile_sidebar` Menu**

**Problem:**
In your `header.php`, you're attempting to display a menu with the `theme_location` set to `'mobile_sidebar'`. However, if this menu location isn't registered in your `functions.php`, WordPress won't recognize it, and the menu won't display.

**Solution:**
Ensure that you register the `mobile_sidebar` menu in your `functions.php` file.

**Example `functions.php`:**

```php
<?php
// functions.php

function my_custom_theme_setup() {
    // Register primary menu
    register_nav_menus( array(
        'primary' => __( 'Primary Menu', 'my-custom-theme' ),
        'mobile_sidebar' => __( 'Mobile Sidebar Menu', 'my-custom-theme' ),
    ) );
}
add_action( 'after_setup_theme', 'my_custom_theme_setup' );
```

---

## **2. CSS Adjustments in `style.css`**

### **Issue 1: Incorrect Z-Index on `.overlay`**

**Problem:**
In your `.overlay` CSS rule, `z-index` is defined **twice**:

```css
.overlay {
    z-index: 1600;
    position: fixed;
    /* ... other styles ... */
    z-index: 1400; /* Duplicate and lower z-index */
    /* ... other styles ... */
}
```

The second `z-index: 1400;` overrides the first, which may cause layering issues.

**Solution:**
Remove the redundant and conflicting `z-index`. Decide on the appropriate stacking order. Typically, the overlay should be below the sidebar but above the main content.

**Corrected `.overlay` CSS:**

```css
/* Overlay to darken the landing page */
.overlay {
    z-index: 1600; /* Set to be below the sidebar */
    position: fixed;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7); /* Semi-transparent black */
    display: none; /* Hidden by default */
    transition: opacity 0.3s ease;
    opacity: 0;
    pointer-events: none;
}
```

### **Issue 2: Sibling Selectors Not Working Due to HTML Structure**

**Problem:**
Initially, the CSS selectors like `.toggle-sidebar:checked ~ .sidebar` and `.toggle-sidebar:checked ~ .overlay` weren't working because the checkbox was not a sibling of `.sidebar` and `.overlay`. After moving the checkbox outside the `<header>`, ensure that the CSS selectors are correctly targeting the elements.

**Solution:**
With the corrected HTML structure, the existing CSS selectors should now work. However, verify that the order of elements in the HTML ensures that `.sidebar` and `.overlay` are **after** the checkbox within the same parent (`<body>`).

**Ensure the Order in HTML:**

```html
<body>
    <input type="checkbox" class="toggle-sidebar" id="toggle-sidebar">

    <header>
        <!-- Header content -->
    </header>

    <label for="toggle-sidebar" class="overlay"></label>

    <div class="sidebar">
        <!-- Sidebar content -->
    </div>

    <div class="main-content">
        <!-- Main content -->
    </div>

    <?php wp_footer(); ?>
</body>
```

**Updated CSS Selectors (if needed):**

No changes are necessary if the HTML order is as above. The existing CSS selectors should now correctly apply.

### **Issue 3: Color Property on `body` Might Be Misleading**

**Problem:**
In your CSS, the `body` has the following:

```css
body {
    font-family: var(--font-family);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--lighter-gray-bg);
}
```

Setting `color` to `var(--lighter-gray-bg)` (which is `#fafafa`, a light gray) can make the text hard to read on light backgrounds.

**Solution:**
Typically, the `color` property sets the default text color. Ensure that it's a contrasting color against your background. If `--lighter-gray-bg` is intended to be a background color, you should set it to `background-color` instead.

**Corrected `body` CSS:**

```css
body {
    font-family: var(--font-family);
    line-height: 1.6;
    background-color: var(--lighter-gray-bg);
    color: var(--darker-gray-text-gray); /* Use a darker color for text */
}
```

### **Issue 4: Hamburger Icon Alignment and Visibility**

**Problem:**
The `.hamburger` has `margin-left: auto;`, which may cause alignment issues within the header, especially with `justify-content: space-between;` already in place. Additionally, ensure that the hamburger icon is properly sized and visible on mobile devices.

**Solution:**
Adjust the alignment and spacing to ensure the hamburger icon is correctly positioned. You might not need `margin-left: auto;` if `justify-content: space-between;` is already handling the spacing.

**Updated `.hamburger` CSS:**

```css
/* Hamburger Menu Styles */
.hamburger {
    display: none;
    flex-direction: column;
    cursor: pointer;
    /* Remove margin-left: auto; */
    z-index: 2700; /* Ensure it's above other elements */
}

.hamburger span {
    background: var(--header-text-light-gray);
    height: 2.2px;
    width: 25px;
    margin: 4px 0; /* Increased margin for better spacing */
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
}
```

### **Issue 5: Transition for Sidebar and Overlay**

**Problem:**
While you have transitions set for `.sidebar` and `.overlay`, ensure that their initial and active states are correctly defined to achieve smooth animations.

**Solution:**
Verify and possibly enhance the transition properties for smoother animations.

**Enhanced CSS for Sidebar and Overlay:**

```css
/* Sidebar Styling */
.sidebar {
    position: fixed;
    top: 0;
    right: -300px; /* Initially hidden off-screen */
    height: 100%;
    width: 300px;
    background-color: rgba(230, 140, 20, 0.95); /* Slightly less transparent for better visibility */
    color: var(--header-text-white);
    box-shadow: -2px 0 5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
    transition: right 0.3s ease;
    z-index: 1700;
    padding: 20px;
    overflow-y: auto;
}

/* Show sidebar when checkbox is checked */
.toggle-sidebar:checked ~ .sidebar {
    right: 0;
}

/* Overlay Effect */
.toggle-sidebar:checked ~ .overlay {
    display: block;
    opacity: 1; /* Transition to this opacity */
    pointer-events: auto;
}
```

### **Issue 6: Accessibility Considerations**

**Problem:**
Using a hidden checkbox to toggle the sidebar can cause accessibility issues. Screen readers might not interpret the checkbox correctly, and keyboard navigation may be hindered.

**Solution:**
Enhance accessibility by adding `aria` attributes and ensuring that the labels have appropriate descriptions.

**Enhanced Accessibility in `header.php`:**

```html
<!-- Checkbox for toggling sidebar -->
<input type="checkbox" class="toggle-sidebar" id="toggle-sidebar" aria-hidden="true">

<!-- Hamburger Icon for Mobile -->
<label for="toggle-sidebar" class="hamburger" aria-label="Open sidebar menu">
    <span></span>
    <span></span>
    <span></span>
</label>

<!-- Overlay to Close Sidebar when Clicked -->
<label for="toggle-sidebar" class="overlay" aria-label="Close sidebar menu"></label>

<!-- Sidebar for Mobile Menu -->
<div class="sidebar" aria-hidden="true">
    <label for="toggle-sidebar" class="close-btn" aria-label="Close sidebar menu">&times;</label>
    <!-- Sidebar content -->
</div>
```

**Note:**
- Added `aria-label` to labels acting as buttons.
- Added `aria-hidden="true"` to the checkbox and sidebar to prevent screen readers from misinterpreting them. You may need to adjust these based on testing with assistive technologies.

---

## **3. Additional Recommendations**

### **1. Optimize Sidebar Content**

Avoid using multiple `<br>` tags for spacing within `.sidebar-extra-content`. Instead, use CSS padding or margin to create the necessary space.

**Example:**

```css
.sidebar-extra-content {
    margin-top: 50px; /* Adjust as needed */
    padding: 20px 0;
    /* Additional styling */
}
```

### **2. Ensure Main Content is Not Hidden Behind Sidebar**

When the sidebar is open, ensure that the main content remains accessible or appropriately obscured by the overlay. You might need to adjust `z-index` values or add transformations to `.main-content` if necessary.

### **3. Responsive Enhancements**

While you have a media query for `max-width: 768px`, consider testing on various device sizes to ensure the layout remains consistent and functional across different screen resolutions.

---

## **Final Assessment**

Due to the incorrect placement of the checkbox within the `<header>`, the CSS selectors intended to toggle the sidebar and overlay do not function as expected. By relocating the checkbox to be a sibling of both `<header>` and `.sidebar`, and addressing the additional issues highlighted above, your theme should achieve the desired mobile-responsive hamburger menu and sidebar functionality without relying on JavaScript.

---

