## **Explanation of the `index.html` Components**

### **1. HTML Structure**

- **Checkbox for Toggling Sidebar:**
  ```html
  <input type="checkbox" class="toggle-sidebar" id="toggle-sidebar" aria-hidden="true">
  ```
  - This hidden checkbox controls the visibility of the sidebar and overlay. It's linked to the hamburger and overlay labels via the `for` attribute.

- **Header Section:**
  ```html
  <header>
      <div class="logo">
          <a href="#">My Logo</a>
      </div>
      <!-- Desktop Navigation -->
      <nav class="desktop-only">
          <ul>
              <li><a href="#">Home</a></li>
              <li>
                  <a href="#">Services</a>
                  <ul>
                      <li><a href="#">Web Design</a></li>
                      <li><a href="#">SEO</a></li>
                      <li><a href="#">Marketing</a></li>
                  </ul>
              </li>
              <li><a href="#">About</a></li>
              <li><a href="#">Contact</a></li>
          </ul>
      </nav>
      <!-- Hamburger Icon for Mobile -->
      <label for="toggle-sidebar" class="hamburger" aria-label="Open sidebar menu">
          <span></span>
          <span></span>
          <span></span>
      </label>
  </header>
  ```
  - **Logo:** Displays your website's logo or name.
  - **Desktop Navigation:** Visible only on larger screens (`desktop-only`). Contains primary navigation links and a submenu under "Services".
  - **Hamburger Icon:** Visible only on smaller screens (via CSS media queries). Clicking it toggles the sidebar.

- **Overlay:**
  ```html
  <label for="toggle-sidebar" class="overlay" aria-label="Close sidebar menu"></label>
  ```
  - A semi-transparent overlay that appears when the sidebar is open. Clicking it will uncheck the checkbox, thereby closing the sidebar.

